{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"AnimationEnvironmentProxy","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"AnimationEnvironment","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Motion20AnimationEnvironmentP","identifier":"doc:\/\/Motion\/documentation\/Motion\/AnimationEnvironment"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Motion extends common AppKit interface elements so that they can be used as animation environments:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSView"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSViewController"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"NSWindow","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"code":"NSWindowController","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSApplication"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The AppKit types above are listed from most to least specific.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Prefer to use the most specific environment whenever possible to ensure the best results for your animations."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if you’re configuring an animation inside of a view controller, you may use the view controller itself"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the environment parameter for your animation:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["override func viewDidLoad() {","    super.viewDidLoad()","","    let anim = BasicAnimation<CGFloat>(enviro